intro:
EXPLANATION OF RESEARCH

 
Title of Project: Predicting Novel Technology Adoption

Principal Investigator: Xiaoqing Wan

Faculty Supervisor: Nichole Lighthall



You are being invited to take part in a research study. Whether you take part is up to you. The purpose of this study is to understand digital technology adoption. We expect that you will be in this online research study for 30 minutes. You will be asked to complete surveys, cognitive games, and to provide information about whether, how often, and why you use various digital technology. Compensation for your participation will be $4.



No identifiable private information will be collected during the study. Retention of data will be more than five years.



In order to participate, you must be: 

• Using a computer or laptop, but not using Safari as your browser• at least 60 years old

• fluent in English

• primarily reside in the U.S.

• have normal or corrected vision

• not diagnosed with dementia, mild cognitive impairment, recent stroke, or recent concussion



The research is voluntary. You are free to withdraw at any time without penalty, but these conditions will prevent you from receiving payment:

• early withdrawal

• failing attention questions

• providing answers that are incomprehensible

• when you did not make a reservation on Prolific prior to completing the survey

• when the Prolific reservation timed out



Study contact for questions about the study or to report a problem: If you have questions, concerns, or complaints: Xiaoqing Wan, doctoral student, Department of Psychology, UCF, by email xiaoqingwan@knights.ucf.edu. Nichole Lighthall, faculty advisor, Nichole.Lighthall@ucf.edu.



IRB contact about your rights in this study or to report a complaint: If you have questions about your rights as a research participant, or have concerns about the conduct of this study, please contact Institutional Review Board (IRB), University of Central Florida, Office of Research, 12201 Research Parkway, Suite 501, Orlando, FL 32826-3246 or by telephone at (407) 823-2901, or email irb@ucf.edu.

imm_intro:
The next task involves listening to an audio clip.
You will hear a set of 10 words and we will ask you to recall as many as you can. We have purposely made the list long so that it will be difficult for anyone to recall all the words -- most people recall just a few. Please listen carefully to the set of words because they will not be repeated. When the audio clip finishes, we will ask you to recall as many of the words as you can, in any order.
